A R70 00 reward is on offer for information that leads to the arrest and subsequent conviction of the person responsible for the murder of Durban musician and nature lover, Simon Milliken, 60, in Burman Bush Nature Reserve on 31 August 2018. This is also a call for anyone attacked or mugged in the Burman Bush Reserve or surrounding areas to provide information about the nature of the attack and a description of the attacker, weapons used, etc. The information you provide may help police solve crimes in the area by identifying possible suspects and the way they operate. Please contact:CrimeStop on 08600 10111 or investigating officer, Segt Mthethwa on 071Â 059 0669. 